
[1]castration

   CASTRATION, n. The act of gelding; the act or practice of making
   eunuchs; the act of taking away the obscene parts of a writing; the act
   of taking out a leaf or sheet of a book. In botany, the cutting off of
   the anthers, or tops of the stamens of flowers, before the ripening of
   the pollen.
